doc.previous: The Younger Futhark became known in Europe as the alphabet of the Norsemen and was studied in the interest of trade and diplomatic contacts referred to as Abecedarium Nordmannicum in Frankish Fulda possibly by Walahfrid Strabo and ogam lochlannach Ogham of the Scandinavians in the Book of Ballymote
